==English==

===Etymology===
[[grid]] + [[lock]]

===Noun===
'''gridlock'''
# A condition of total, interlocking [[traffic]] [[congestion]] on the [[street]]s or [[highway]]s of a crowded city, in which no one can move because everyone is in someone else's way.
# On a smaller scale: the situation in which cars enter a [[traffic light|signal]]-controlled [[intersection]] too late during the [[green light]] cycle, and are unable to clear the intersection (due to congestion in the next [[block]]) when the light turns [[red]], thus blocking the cross traffic when it's their turn to go.  Repeated at enough intersections, this phenomenon can lead to citywide gridlock.
# Figuratively and by extension, any [[paralysis]] of a complex system due to severe congestion, conflict, or [[deadlock]].

